\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1408191 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1408191 
\par YOUTH/EDUCATION 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13459989 34. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1408191 The whole operation of currency reform afforded an excellent opportunity to the local authorities to rescue the many youths who a
re homeless, parentless, and until now have lived only through the black market. Their numbers are alleged to be very high, and their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13459989 effect}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1408191 
 on the moral standards of future German admit life is expected to be very bad indeed unless strong action is taken immediately to educate and discipline them.
\par 
\par PRESS/WIRELESS 
\par 
\par 35. An article on the London Slums published in the HAMBURGER ECHO of 11th June 1948 has brought much sarcastic comment from the general public. This article described the filth, drunken
ness, crime, prostitution, etc., in a particular quarter in London, and the general reaction has been that Britain is far behind Germany in matters of social welfare, that she was no doubt now attempting to drag Germany down to that level, and that she ou
ght to clean up her own house before attempting to do anything in Germany.
\par 
\par RUMOURS 
\par 
\par 36. Tinned horseflesh, used during the war to feed Army dogs, is now being delivered for consumption by the German people.
\par 
\par 37. The salaries of the Burgermeister, Senators, and Senats-syndici are going to be increased despite the new value of the Mark under currency reform.
\par 
\par 38. There are many rumours that the British, Americans, and French are soon to withdraw from Berlin.
\par 
\par 39. A war between East and West is now unavoidable and will start before the end of the year.
\par 
\par 40. Troops and equipment are being massed all along the border and the first attacks will be made through Lubeck and the Harz Mountains.
\par 
\par 41. Russia is now mass-producing atom bombs.
\par 
\par 42. Russia is printing enormous numbers of the new Mark in use in the Western Zones, which will soon be flooded with these Marks so that both the currency and the Marshal Plan will be completely sabotaged.
\par 
\par MISCELLANEOUS 
\par 
\par 43. The reason given by the British authorities for returning to the Soviet sector of Berlin a Russian Colonel who had fled to Britain (namely that he wished voluntarily to be sent there), is treated with open disbelief and has greatly 
shaken public confidence in Britain's desire to maintain a firm stand against Soviet demands and impositions. It is now said that Britain would not hesitate to deliver to the Soviet authorities any fleeing German sought by them.
\par 
\par 44. The acquittal of P
ETERSON, BUSCH, and SCHULZ and others charged with crimes against humanity is quoted as yet another example of the unsatisfactory manner in which courts are handling such cases, and there is the usual criticism that the "big fish" are acquitted while the 
"small fry" are severely punished.
\par 
\par 45. Consequent on the publicity given to recent crimes in which armed Poles and Yugoslavs have been involved, there has been a general outcry that the time has come for these people, many of whom came to Germany of th
eir own free will, either to be returned forcibly to their own countries or to have their many special privileges taken from them. Immediately after the capitulation, their armed robbery, murder, rape, etc., were an understandable reaction to the treatmen
t
 they had suffered under the Nazis, but at this late date the Occupation Forces should take immediate action to curb these activities. France's campaign to recruit German workers in addition to the many thousands of prisoners of war which she still holds 
is discussed as a cunning method to rob an impoverished Germany 'of her few remaining skilled craftsmen and thus keep her indefinitely in subjection.
\par 
\par 46. The use of so much paper for forms and propaganda material in connection with "Volksbegehren" is deplored by a very large section of this paper-starved community.
\par 
\par (A. S. Barnes, A.I.G.)
\par for Deputy Inspector General
\par 
